title: About Me
text:
I recently completed my Master’s of Data Science (MDS) at the University of British Columbia and am passionate about machine learning, statistical modelling, team building, and active living! I am a creative problem solver who is experienced building data pipelines, statistical models, and dashboards. I am skilled in Python and R, and have experience with SQL.
In my down time I enjoy travelling, sports, taking in local stand-up comedy shows, and exploring all that Vancouver has to offer!
Below are a few highlights from my educational journey, but for more details on my previous experiences check out my resume!

title: Projects
text:
Dreamhouse - A Real-Estate Dashboard


A dashboard built using Plotly Dash to help newcomers to real-estate explore the markets of the 50 most populous cities in the US.













Predicting high-potential FIFA players using individual performance data


A classifier model to identify soccer players with high potential.













quanteda Python Package


A package for simplifying the EDA of time-series data.













“Defense wins championships”: Coach’s fact or fallacy?


In this blog post, I use logistic regression and data from 10 NCAA men’s basketball seasons to assess the validity of a common coaching adage.

Predicting Physical Performance - Vancouver Whitecaps FC  - Constructed a data pipeline using Python, R, and SQL that queries new data from Snowflake, preprocesses it, feeds it to a series of linear mixed-effects models to predict first-team player physical performance, and saves the predictions back to Snowflake as a new table.
